class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"5bff4119f90d7d493ef77aa9b712be24fab389e3","tid":2028292,"uid":76591,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-05-21T23:00:39.000Z","msg":"係啊中國，中華民國吖嘛<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"75da8b3ca5465836eb55cfacc6085b7b886d2801","tid":2028292,"uid":158888,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-05-21T23:24:14.000Z","msg":"當台灣死㗎<br />\n南韓支那兩個繼續打飛機<br />\n<br />\n超越南韓，台灣登上 2019 年全球最大半導體設備市場<br />\n報告中指出，台灣穩坐 2019 年全球半導體設備的最大市場，銷售金額增加 68%，來到 171.2 億美元，超越南韓成為市場上的龍頭。中國則是繼續保持第二大設備市場的地位，銷售金額為 134.5 億美元，南韓下跌 44%，以 99.7 億美元位居排行第三。而相對日本、歐洲和世界其他地區新設備市場的萎縮態勢，北美設備銷售額 2019 年躍升了 40%， 達到 81.5 億美元，為該區連續第 3 年成長。<br />\n<a href=\"https://technews.tw/2020/04/15/semi-says-worldwide-semiconductor-equipment-market/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftechnews.tw%2F2020%2F04%2F15%2Fsemi-says-worldwide-semiconductor-equipment-market%2F&d=ppuFFh6piFuOrul45s7BzbJtyMJyNHaGyUrVEdcKl1A%3D&h=eba589f4\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://technews.tw/2020/04/15/semi-says-worldwide-semiconductor-equipment-market/</a>"},{"pid":"4451a3939e86dfc4e5cd1cec05aec4ca31308ac5","tid":2028292,"uid":34189,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"ebb7bb4bbccb1082691b3f1117621ce3b4a416ea","tid":2028292,"uid":267423,"like":3,"dislike":1,"score":2,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-05-21T17:39:19.000Z","msg":"14納米做最終霸主?<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-05-21T23:33:23.000Z","msg":"買intel amd磨走logo自煮燃發<img src=\"/assets/faces/mouse/solution.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"1e457f7dacd1e69a0cb4551a3b9d2bf678b68249","tid":2028292,"uid":224882,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"4451a3939e86dfc4e5cd1cec05aec4ca31308ac5","tid":2028292,"uid":34189,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"ebb7bb4bbccb1082691b3f1117621ce3b4a416ea","tid":2028292,"uid":267423,"like":3,"dislike":1,"score":2,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-05-21T17:39:19.000Z","msg":"14納米做最終霸主?<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-05-21T23:33:23.000Z","msg":"買intel amd磨走logo自煮燃發<img src=\"/assets/faces/mouse/solution.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-05-21T23:44:06.000Z","msg":"磨走個logo都要好多技術架<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/hate.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"45e555af23b9e97b852fa3d1bbe11d66d26c7db5","tid":2028292,"uid":254383,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"d7ffc2bfdd10e79823711fd6a73657c4ff498a72","tid":2028292,"uid":27250,"like":5,"dislike":0,"score":5,"quote":{"pid":"704dc02c3c60ca59da0a0c731d42055f118b4c9d","tid":2028292,"uid":141151,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-05-21T17:32:01.000Z","msg":"中美半導體戰三星受惠？中官媒：中國才是最終霸主<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://technews.tw/2020/05/21/semiconductor-war-china/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftechnews.tw%2F2020%2F05%2F21%2Fsemiconductor-war-china%2F&d=ppuFFh6piFuOrul45s7BzbJtyMJyNHaGyUrVEdcKl1A%3D&h=83c98d2f\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://technews.tw/2020/05/21/semiconductor-war-china/</a><br />\n<br />\n三星電子（Samsung Electronics）副總裁李在鎔（Lee Jae-yong）日前訪視西安半導體廠，時機正值中美再度在半導體產業上演角力戰，外界猜測三星將成為主要受惠者，也引發中國官媒高度關注，透過報導向南韓發出警告。<br />\n<br />\n韓媒《BusinessKorea》報導，李在鎔 18 日訪問三星西安半導體廠，於 19 日返回南韓。20 日，中國官媒《環球網》發表題為《三星副總裁為何訪西安半導體工廠》的報導，當中提到，李在鎔選擇西安為疫情期間出訪第一站，目的是強調實現「半導體願景 2030」（Vision 2030）的決心。<br />\n<br />\n2019 年 4 月，三星宣示啟動「半導體願景 2030」計畫，誓言在 2030 年前總計砸下 133 兆韓圜，衝刺發展邏輯 IC 等非記憶體晶片，以及晶圓代工事業，目標是在 2030 年登上全球系統半導體廠龍頭。<br />\n<br />\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\"><span style=\"color: red;\">《BusinessKorea》報導指出，《環球網》報導真正想傳達的訊息，除了批評美國對中國實施禁令外，也是為了警告南韓，中國才是最終的半導體霸主。</span></span></strong><br />\n<br />\n報導寫道，美國試圖扼殺中國在半導體領域的地位，要求台積電等晶片製造商在美國設廠，藉此重組半導體產業的生態系統。報導還提到中國在半導體市場的重要性，指中國約占全球半導體需求的 23%。若將中美技術脫鉤，將導致美國半導體行業全球市占率下降 18%、整體營收下降 37%、研發支出減少 60%、就業機會減少 12.4 萬個。<br />\n<br />\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\"><span style=\"color: red;\">報導警告：「美國將失去全球領導地位。而南韓短期內可能超過美國成為世界半導體領先者，但從長遠看，中國最終可能取得領導地位。」</span></span></strong><br />\n<br />\n《金融時報》報導，雖然疫情及中美角力造成半導體市場的不確定性，三星仍計劃在晶片生產方面進行數十億美元的新投資。<br />\n<br />\n訪視完西安半導體廠後，李在鎔重申，將加碼 80 億美元，進行西安廠第二階段的擴張。此外，三星 21 日發表新聞稿宣佈，將南韓建造新晶圓廠，用於生產 5G、人工智慧（AI）和高效能運算（High Performance Computing，HPC）的高階晶片。<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/support.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/support.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/support.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/support.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/support.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/support.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-05-21T17:34:25.000Z","msg":"係？美帝嘅小弟日本一話唔賣材料俾南韓，跪咗喎"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-05-21T23:46:57.000Z","msg":"明明日本先係獨家上游供應商<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"}]}